Fantastic! I am definitely going to make this again. Made this for a labor day weekend BBQ party for 5 families on our block. So, used a 5 lb pork tenderloin, cut up into 1 inch chunks for kebabs. Multiplied the sauce recipe by about 5 x (except less on the salt, and less on the hot pepper - only had jalapeno on hand) and cooked it down longer as others had recommended. Used half the sauce to marinate the pork cubes overnight. Then made kebabs with the pork, sweet onion, red pepper & pineapple. Used the remaining sauce to baste the kebabs (though still had left over). The meat was SO tender & flavorful and the sauce is just fantastic. I would make the sauce alone just to have on hand for stir fries and other dishes. WOW!

