Rating: 3
I modified this recipe and served it to 24 for lunch yesterday. They raved - here are my suggested changes: double the recipe and simmer sauce at least 15 minutes. Allow to cool slightly, it will thicken as it cools. Marinate pork tenderloin (or chops)that are cut in 1 inch cubes for at least one hour, and up to 6 hours in half of sauce, reserving rest of sauce for serving. Remove pork from marinade and skewer with red bell peppers and green onions. Grill over high heat (put foil on grill where skewers are exposed to prevent buring, until nicely charred, turn and repeat, about 8-10 minutes. I plated over cashew jasmine rice and drizzled with remaining sauce. It was a hit.

